Nigerian Afrosoul singer, Sadiq Onifade aka WurlD has set a date for his highly anticipated sophomore album entitled, ‘My WorlD With U.’ The artist, who recently released a single, ‘Let You Down,’ from the upcoming album, announced the date for album release. “My WorlD With U by WurlD, out on March 11.” He also hinted at the possibility of releasing another single before the album release.   Sotayo completes leadership training course     Why my marriage to Kanye West failed, by Kim Kardashian     American rapper Eve welcomes first child with hubby   In August 2021, WurlD released two love songs, ‘Spunk’ and ‘Stamina’ off his debut album, a 19-tracker project. On the inspiration behind the body of work, the Universal Music Group signee said it’s is his most personal project. - Advertisement - “My WorlD With U is gonna take everyone on the wildest emotional ride. I’m flawed and vulnerable as I’ve ever been while taking the listeners through my private life journey. This is my most personal project to date.”